President Obama will host the 2012-2013 NCAA Division I Men's and Women's Champions at the White House on March 10. The event will be held on the South Lawn and will be open to the press. The President will congratulate the student athletes from various schools across the country for their achievements in both academics and sports. The event will be live-streamed on obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/live. The teams expected to attend include Duke University, Indiana University, Oklahoma State University, Princeton University, Stanford University, University of Alabama, University of California Irvine, University of Colorado Boulder, University of Kansas, University of Minnesota, University of North Carolina, University of Oklahoma, University of Southern California, University of Virginia, West Virginia University, and Yale University.